# Portfolio `/past` project pages

## Required sections (in order)

Every **project deep-dive** (`app/past/<slug>/page.tsx`) must include:

1. **Header** — Eyebrow badge, title, primary actions: **View source** (GitHub), **Live** (external), **View Gallery** (`<Link href="/gallery">` with orange `ImageIcon`, matching Altar / other pages).

2. **The Discovery** — Section heading with `Search` icon; lead copy explaining the problem space / insight.

3. **The Purpose** — Sidebar-style card (right column on md+) with `Sparkles` icon and short italic purpose statement.

4. **Quote** — Pull-quote block with `MessageSquareQuote` inside the Discovery column (same pattern as Altar).

5. **The Friction** — Card with `ShieldAlert`; what was wrong with status quo.

6. **The Solve** — Card with `Zap`; what you built / how it addresses friction.

7. **Technical Snapshot** — `Terminal` icon + heading; grid of label/value pairs (stack, deploy, core loop, etc.).

8. **Footer** — “End of Transmission” strip (optional but consistent on completed pages).

Match spacing and Tailwind patterns from `app/past/altar/page.tsx` unless there is a deliberate redesign.

## `/past` hub (`app/past/page.tsx`) accent colors

Assign **one Tailwind hue per project** for folder icon + hover arrow. **Do not reuse** an existing project’s hue.

Current reservation:

| Project      | Hue     | Classes (example)                    |
|-------------|---------|--------------------------------------|
| Orbit       | emerald | `bg-emerald-500/10 text-emerald-400` |
| Altar       | violet  | `bg-violet-500/10 text-violet-400`   |
| Mustafa.ai  | cyan    | `bg-cyan-500/10 text-cyan-400`        |
| QuickBooks  | blue    | `bg-blue-500/10 text-blue-400`       |

For a **new** project, pick an unused hue (e.g. **rose**, **orange**, **fuchsia**, **amber**) and add a row to this rule.

## Home Past pillar order (Archive)

The three cards follow **recency**, not a permanent “flagship.” **Newest completed project first.**

The small status label on each card (bottom right) should read **`Completed`** for every project in this pillar—including shipped apps that still have a live URL—so the Archive reads consistently.

- **With Supabase:** `app/page.tsx` uses whatever `projects` returns, already ordered by `created_at` descending—**do not** hardcode a slug to slot 0.
- **Empty DB fallback:** `pastPillarFallbackByRecency` in `app/page.tsx` is a **manually maintained newest-first** list; when you ship something newer than Orbit, **put that entry first** in the array.
